    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I’d like to help with maintenance of nvim.net if the current maintainers are open to it.\n\nInitial scope I’d propose:\n- triage existing issues/PRs\n- get the build/tests passing on current .NET\n- update CI\n- modernise project files without changing public API\n- regenerate/update bindings against current Neovim API if needed\n- document the current support status\n\nI’m not proposing large design changes up front. I’d start with small compatibility-preserving PRs and use those to establish trust before asking for any broader permissions.\n\nWhy I'm looking to help here is that I'm primarily a senior .NET dev, and I use F# a lot in my free time. What I'd want to eventually look to add is a native F# emitter target for the client generator, and a broader abstraction of the generator to support multiple emitters. Instead of competing with the official nvim.net package, I want to contribute directly to this project to help support its modernisation and compatability.",
